$ Preprocessor: Stringify macros and identifiers

The single hash (`#`) directive creates a quoted string from the value of a preprocessor macro.

gh|about-preprocessor|/hash/stringify.c||

The program prints:
code {
QuoteIdent(int)    = int
QuoteIdent(FRUIT)  = FRUIT
QuoteMacro(FRUIT)  = strawberry
QuoteMacro(I_LIKE) = strawberry
QuoteMacro(int)    = int
code }

sa:

  Compare with `##` which → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/preprocessor/macros/concatenate[concatenates two macro values].

  → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/preprocessor/macros
